  "provenance": "Default basis for Uganda/EDGE projects. Derived from IFC EDGE materials methodology (World Bank Group EDGE) cross-checked against the ICE database v3.0 (Hammond & Jones, cradle-to-gate A1-A3 kgCO2e/kg) multiplied by a representative in-place density. Uganda sourcing notes applied: structural concrete uses high-clinker CEM I (no significant GGBS/PFA substitution typical in UK mixes, so figures sit at the upper end); structural steel and aluminium are predominantly imported (world-average primary-route factors, not UK recycled-content); masonry is local fired-clay brick or concrete block. These are INDICATIVE corporate defaults — where a material carries a verified EPD (boq_epd_map.json) or its own STING_EMB_CARBON_NR parameter, those win. Override per-project at <project>/_BIM_COORD/carbon_factors_ug.json (additive by key).",
